    "_comment": "Cinema Worldbuilder example: VIDEO-TO-VIDEO refine (SDEdit) on LTX 2.3 22B distilled Q2_K GGUF. Adapted verbatim from the known-good ltx23_warp_v2v.json stack: keeps VHS_LoadVideo -> VAEEncode and the SplitSigmasDenoise (denoise 0.5) SDEdit path. ONLY change vs reference: the positive prompt text is wired from CinemaWorldbuilder_PromptComposer instead of being hardcoded; the negative prompt stays literal. PLACEHOLDER: edit VHS_LoadVideo 'video' to your source clip in ComfyUI/input/ (default 'warp_00_dolly_in_filled.mp4'). Edit the Cinema node inputs in the UI. Audio is decoded and muxed into VHS_VideoCombine. Requires the same LTX 2.3 models as cinema_ltx23_t2v.json."
